00:02:08.860 --> 00:02:11.120
we know why we're learning this language.

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:12.870
We know what the purposes.

00:02:12.870 --> 00:02:17.770
So this kind of makes it a bit less tedious because every time we learn new vocab or new

00:02:17.770 --> 00:02:18.450
grammar,

00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:21.760
we know that it's something that can be used in real situations,

00:02:21.760 --> 00:02:25.930
and we find ways to apply it in real situations and we can set up our own schedule.

00:02:25.930 --> 00:02:28.660
So we know that if we learn a new grammatical rule,

00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:29.480
we can decide.

00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:29.920
OK,

00:02:29.920 --> 00:02:31.340
this means that I can use it in this.

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:32.270
In that situation,

00:02:32.270 --> 00:02:33.490
you can go out and use it,

00:02:33.490 --> 00:02:36.300
and suddenly you find yourself improving that much more.

